Alembic migration environment for VCAI (single-database configuration).

Location: this directory lives at the REPO ROOT (VCAI/migrations), with alembic.ini
at VCAI/alembic.ini. It is named "migrations" (not "alembic") so it does not
shadow the installed alembic package when commands run from the repo root.
Run all alembic commands from the repo root.

The database URL is loaded in env.py from backend.config.get_settings().database_url
(the same .env the app uses), not from alembic.ini.

Common commands (run from repo root, using the env that has the project deps):
    alembic upgrade head      # apply migrations
    alembic downgrade -1      # roll back the most recent migration
    alembic current           # show current revision
    alembic history           # list revisions

If `alembic` resolves to the wrong Python (ModuleNotFoundError: pydantic_settings),
run it through the project interpreter instead, e.g.:
    python -c "from alembic.config import main; main(argv=['upgrade','head'])"

The first revision (0001_tenancy_baseline) is hand-written to ADD only the new
multi-tenancy tables and users.company_id. It deliberately does NOT recreate the
pre-existing tables (users, sessions, personas, etc.), which already exist on the
live database.
